<P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#dcdeed><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/usyrinxcc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>SyrinxCC</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Tim the Enchanter</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>posts: </FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>18</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#333333>4/20/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#333333>7:30:21 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Planar loot for Clerics</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">I don't have a high level cleric, but I have been the raid leader for 6 Hate raids.<br>
<br>
The policy I use on my raids, is that it is my job to reimburse all clerics for peridot usage.  I ask the clerics to keep track of the peridots they use, and let me know what I owe them at the end of the raid.  I bring a 10 slot backpack full of peridots with me.  It is there mostly to make sure that no cleric runs out of peridots.  I also use it to start paying clerics at the end of the raid, but I have found with a 6 group raid, we will typically go through about 250 peridots.<br>
<br>
As the raid leader I also pay for all the teleport stones.  (6 groups takes 7 teleport stones, plus another couple to get replacements late in the raid).  The total cost for a raid is about 4500pp.  I then sell the jewelry and non-rare gems to cover those costs.  Any rare gems (diamonds, blue diamonds, jacinth or black sapphire), are used for resist jewelry for the guild.  If the raid is a success, I make platinum.  If the raid is a failure I lose platinum.<br>
